    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is the identification of complications in diabetes mellitus pediatric
      patients and to compare the clinical, anthropometric, and biochemical characteristics between
      children in the different types of diabetes mellitus.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Diabetes mellitus is characterized by hyperglycemia resulting from defects in insulin
      secretion and/or insulin resistance in target tissues. This study identify the influence of
      pathogenic factors on the evolution of diabetes mellitus and in the presence of chronic
      complications.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
